SEMDL Help Topic: reference normalize

Usage:
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> [--stdout]`
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> --dry-run [--format inline|sidecar]`
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> --out <output.ssd> [--format inline|sidecar] [--dry-run]`

Status:
- `--stdout` returns canonical inline output from `.ssd` with an optional paired `.ssm`.
- Bare apply remains inline-only and removes the sibling `.ssm` on paired input after writing canonical inline output.
- `--dry-run` and `--out` default to inline output, but `--format sidecar` previews or writes a split `.ssd` + `.ssm` pair without modifying the source files.
- `--stdout` and bare apply do not accept `--format` in this slice.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`

Sample:
- `ssd normalize docs/examples/normalize-source.ssd --out docs/examples/normalized-output.ssd`
- `ssd normalize docs/examples/normalize-source.ssd --out docs/examples/normalized-sidecar.ssd --format sidecar`
